pls.text:
We found nine studies, including 5209 participants who used nicotine-containing vapes. Eight studies took place in the USA and one in Italy. Treatments used to help people stop vaping were:
two types of nicotine replacement therapy used together, such as patches and gum (otherwise known as combination nicotine replacement therapy);    cytisine (a medicine to help people stop smoking);   varenicline (a medicine to help people stop smoking);   a plan to help people reduce the nicotine in their vapes and the amount they were vaping over time;    a text message-based intervention.
